contents.desc: Tips for shooting videos with a model/subject📲: - I sometimes recommend shooting in your phone’s wide lens to capture some of the scene - (use 0.5) - Always have motion in mind (ex: move 180° from your subject left to right or move front and back) adding some type of movement will make it more engaging  - Keep it nice and stable - avoid shaky footage - Maintain your subject/model centered and exactly vertical to you (turn on your camera Grid to help frame) - Bonus Tip (if posting for social) - Show some of the behind-the-scenes of how you captured the shot - sometimes getting the shot can be a lot more entertaining than the actual shot itself  Save these for later!✅✌🏻📲 #shotoniphone #dji #videography #filmmaking
